==A==

{{glossary}}
{{term|term= '''[[abiotic component]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Any non-living chemical or physical part of the environment that affects living organisms and the functioning of ecosystems, such as the [[Earth's atmosphere|atmosphere]] and water resources.}}

{{term|term= '''[[abscisic acid]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A [[plant hormone]] with the formula C<sub>15</sub>H<sub>20</sub>O<sub>4</sub>.}}

{{term|term= '''[[abscission]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The shedding of flowers, leaves and/or fruit following formation of scar tissue in a plant.}}

{{term|term= '''[[absolute zero]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The lowest theoretically attainable temperature, at which the [[kinetic energy]] of atoms and molecules is minimal. It is equivalent to 0 [[kelvin]]s, or −273.15 [[degrees Celsius]], or −459.67 [[degrees Fahrenheit]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[absorption (skin)|absorption]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A process in which one substance permeates another. A [[fluid]] permeates or is dissolved by a liquid or solid. Skin absorption is a route by which substances can enter the body through the skin.}}

{{term|term= '''[[absorption spectrum]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The spectrum of [[electromagnetic radiation]] that has passed through a medium which absorbs radiation of certain [[wavelength]]s.}}

{{term|term= '''[[abyssal zone]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The deep [[sea]] (2000 meters or more) where there is no light.}}

{{term|term= '''[[acclimatization]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Adaptation to a new [[climate]], as with a new temperature or altitude or environment.}}

{{term|term= '''[[acetyl-CoA]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A molecule that is involves in many biochemical reactions in [[protein]], [[carbohydrate]] and lipid metabolism.}}

{{term|term= '''[[acetylcholine]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An organic molecule that functions as a [[neurotransmitter]] in the brain and body of many types of animals, including humans.}}

{{term|term= '''[[acid precipitation]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= [[Rain]] or any other form of precipitation containing [[acid]]s that form in the atmosphere when industrial gas emissions (especially [[sulfur dioxide]] and [[nitrogen oxide]]s) combine with [[Properties of water|water]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[acoelomate]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An animal, such as a [[flatworm]] or a [[jellyfish]], that lacks a fluid-filled body cavity between the body wall and digestive tract (the [[coelom]]) Rather, semi-solid mesodermal tissues between the gut and body wall hold the animal's organs in place.}}

{{term|term= '''[[acrosome]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An organelle that expands over the anterior half of the head in the [[spermatozoa]] (sperm cells) of many animals including humans.}}

{{term|term= '''[[actin]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= One of the [[protein]]s into which [[actomyosin]] can be split; can exist in either a globular or a fibrous form.}}

{{term|term= '''[[action potential]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The local [[voltage]] change across the [[cell wall]] as a [[nerve impulse]] is transmitted.}}

{{term|term= '''[[activation energy]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The [[energy]] that an atomic system must acquire before a process (such as an emission or reaction) can occur.}}

{{term|term= '''[[active site]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The part of an [[enzyme]] or [[antibody]] where the [[chemical reaction]] occurs.}}

{{term|term= '''[[active transport]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Transport of a substance (as a protein or [[drug]]) across a [[cell membrane]] against the [[concentration gradient]]; unlike [[passive transport]], it requires an expenditure of energy.}}

{{term|term= '''[[adaptive immune system]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= One of two main [[immunity (medical)|immunity]] strategies found in vertebrates that inhibits or eliminates [[pathogen]]s through the actions of highly specialized systemic cells and processes.}}

{{term|term= '''[[adaptive radiation]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The process in which organisms diversify rapidly from an ancestral species into a multitude of new forms, particularly when a change in the [[Environment (biophysical)|environment]] makes new resources available, creates new challenges, or opens new environmental niches.}}

{{term|term= '''[[adenine]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= a [[purine]]-derived nucleobase.}}

{{term|term= '''[[adenosine triphosphate]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= a [[nucleotide]] derived from [[adenosine]] that occurs in muscle tissue; the major source of energy for cellular reactions. The chemical formula for ATP is C<sub>10</sub>H<sub>16</sub>N<sub>5</sub>O<sub>13</sub>P<sub>3</sub>.}}

{{term|term= '''[[adenylate cyclase]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An enzyme that catalyzes the formation of [[Cyclic adenosine monophosphate|cyclic AMP]] from ATP.}}

{{term|term= '''[[adipose tissue]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The loose connective tissue, also known as body fat or fat, that is made of mostly [[adipocytes]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[aerobic organism|aerobic]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Depending on free [[oxygen]] or air.}}

{{term|term= '''[[aerobiology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The study of organic particles, such as bacteria, fungal spores, very small insects, pollen grains and viruses, which are passively transported by the air.}}

{{term|term= '''[[agriculture]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The practice of cultivating land, growing food, and raising stock.}}

{{term|term= '''[[agrobiology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The study of [[plant nutrition]] and growth, especially as a way to increase crop yield.}}

{{term|term= '''[[allopatric speciation]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= It is a form of speciation that occurs when biological populations of the same species become isolated from each other to an extent that prevents or interferes with genetic interchange. }}

{{term|term= '''[[allosteric enzyme]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= These are [[enzymes]] that change their conformational ensemble upon binding of an effector, which results in an apparent change in binding affinity at a different ligand binding site. }}

{{term|term= '''[[amino acid]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A class of [[organic compound]]s containing an [[amine|amino group]] and a [[carboxylic acid]] group.}}

{{term|term= '''[[amniote]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Organisms that produce an [[egg]] composed of shell and membranes that creates a protected environment in which the [[embryo]] can develop out of water.}}

{{term|term= '''[[amphiphile]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= a chemical compound that has both hydrophilic and lipophilic  properties.}}

{{term|term= '''[[analogous structures]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= .}}

{{term|term= '''[[anatomy]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The branch of [[Morphology (biology)|morphology]] that deals with the structure of animals.}}

{{term|term= '''[[aneuploidy]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The presence of an abnormal number of chromosomes in a cell.}}

{{term|term= '''[[antibiotic]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A type of antimicrobial drug used in the treatment and prevention of bacterial infections. Also called an ''antibacterial''.}}

{{term|term= '''[[Transfer RNA#Anticodon|anticodon]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A unit made up of three nucleotides that correspond to the three bases of the codon on the mRNA.}}

{{term|term= '''[[arachnology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The scientific study of [[spiders]], [[scorpion]]s, [[pseudoscorpion]]s, and [[Opiliones|harvestmen]], collectively called [[arachnid]]s.}}

{{term|term= '''[[Selective breeding|artificial selection]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Professionals study the [[genotype]] and [[phenotype]] of parent organisms in the hope of producing a [[Hybrid (biology)|hybrid]] that possesses many of the desirable characteristics found in their parents. Also known as ''selective breeding''.}}

{{term|term= '''[[asexual reproduction]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A type of [[reproduction]] involving a single parent that results in offspring that are genetically identical to the parent.}}

{{term|term= '''[[astrobiology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The branch of biology concerned with the effects of outer space on living organisms and the search for extraterrestrial life.}}

{{term|term= '''[[atom]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The smallest component of an [[chemical element|element]] having the chemical properties of the element.}}

{{term|term= '''[[autoimmunity]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The system of immune responses of an organism against its own healthy cells and tissues.}}

{{term|term= '''[[autotrophic]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=  ''auto'' means "self" and ''trophe'' means "nourishing or producing".}}

{{glossary end}}

