{{term|term= '''[[insulin]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Insulin helps keeps your blood sugar level from getting too high (hyperglycemia) or too low (hypoglycemia). ... After you eat food and your blood sugar level rises, cells in your pancreas (known as beta cells) are signaled to release insulin into your bloodstream.}}

{{term|term= '''[[interferon]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A group of signaling proteins made and released by host cells in response to the presence of several pathogens, such as viruses, bacteria, parasites, and also tumor cells. In a typical scenario, a virus-infected cell will release interferons causing nearby cells to heighten their antiviral defenses.}}

{{term|term= '''[[integrative biology]]'''}}
