{{term|term= '''[[ionic bond]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The complete transfer of valence electron(s) between atoms. It is a type of chemical bond that generates two oppositely charged ions. In ionic bonds, the metal loses electrons to become a positively charged cation, whereas the nonmetal accepts those electrons to become a negatively charged anion.}}

{{term|term= '''[[isomer]]'''}}
