{{term|term= '''[[metaphase]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The third phase of mitosis, in which duplicated genetic material carried in the nucleus of a parent cell is separated into two identical daughter cells. During metaphase, the cell's chromosomes align themselves in the middle of the cell through a type of cellular "tug of war".}}

{{term|term= '''[[microbiology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The study of microscopic organisms, such as bacteria, viruses, archaea, fungi and protozoa. This discipline includes fundamental research on the biochemistry, physiology, cell biology, ecology, evolution and clinical aspects of microorganisms, including the host response to these agents.}}

{{term|term= '''[[microevolution]]'''}}
