{{term|term= '''[[mitosis]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The process by which a eukaryotic cell nucleus splits in two, followed by division of the parent cell into two daughter cells. The word "mitosis" means "threads", and it refers to the threadlike appearance of chromosomes as the cell prepares to divide. Compare [[binary fission]] in prokaryotes.}}

{{term|term= '''[[molarity]]'''}}
