{{term|term= '''[[molecule]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The smallest particle in a chemical element or compound that has the chemical properties of that element or compound. Molecules are made up of atoms that are held together by chemical bonds. These bonds form as a result of the sharing or exchange of electrons among atoms.}}

{{term|term= '''[[molecular biology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The branch of biology concerning biological activity at the molecular level. The field of molecular biology overlaps with biology and chemistry and in particular with genetics and biochemistry.}}

{{term|term= '''[[molecular physics]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Molecular physics is the study of the physical properties of molecules, the chemical bonds between atoms As well As the molecular dynamics. Its most important experimental techniques are the various types of spectroscopy; scattering is also used. The field is closely related to atomic physics and overlaps greatly with theoretical chemistry, physical chemistry and chemical physics.}}

{{term|term= '''[[molecular switch]]'''}}
