{{term|term= '''[[motor neuron]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A neuron whose cell body is situated in the motor [[Motor cortex|cortex]], [[brainstem]] or the [[spinal cord]], and whose axon (fiber) projects to the spinal cord or outside of the spinal cord to directly or indirectly control effector organs, mainly muscles and glands.}}

{{term|term= '''[[mucous membrane]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A membrane that lines various cavities in the body and covers the surface of [[internal organs]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[multicellular organism]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A organism that consists of more than one [[Cell (biology)|cell]], in contrast to unicellular organisms.}}

{{term|term= '''[[muon]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The muon is an unstable subatomic particle with a mean lifetime of 2.2 µS. Among all known unstable subatomic particles, only the neutron (lasting around 15 minutes) and some atomic nuclei have a longer decay lifetime; others decay significantly faster.}}

{{term|term= '''[[mycology]]'''}}
