{{term|term= '''[[SI units]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A system of fundamental physical units (SI units) widely used in the sciences and including the metre, kilogram, second, ampere, kelvin, candela, and mole, together with a set of prefixes to indicate multiplication or division by a power of ten.}}

{{term|term= '''[[Sociality]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The degree to which individuals in an animal population tend to associate in social groups and form cooperative societies.}}

{{term|term= '''[[sociobiology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A field of scientific study that is based on the hypothesis that social behavior has resulted from evolution and attempts to explain and examine social behavior within that context.}}

